    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>YONKERS: MORE MONEY FOR SCHOOLS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York Gov George Pataki asks Education Department to release $1.8 million in state aid to Yonkers school system, which faces $26 million budget shortfall (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Gov. George E. Pataki has asked the Education Department to release $1.8 million in state aid to the Yonkers schools. Several weeks ago, the school system faced a $26 million budget shortfall. But the governor pledged up to $10 million earlier this month as a down payment on a settlement of the Yonkers school desegregation case, and the district has made other budget cuts to eliminate the shortfall. Yonkers received an $18 million increase in state school aid this year, nearly twice the statewide average of 8.7 percent.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
